midcomSrvMIB.description: This MIB module defines a set of basic objects for monitoring and configuring MIDCOM servers on middleboxes that support MIDCOM. Such middleboxes may be firewalls and network address translators. This MIB module does not implement portions of the MIDCOM protocol, but is the MIDCOM SERVER MIB module for monitoring instances of the MIDCOM protocol. There are three groups of managed objects defined by this MIB module: - objects describing the used middlebox resources on a per MIDCOM policy rule base - objects describing the used firewall configuration on a per MIDCOM policy rule base - objects providing statistical information about the MIDCOM MIB module Copyright (C) The Internet Society (2003). This version of this MIB module is part of RFC yyyy; see the RFC itself for full legal notices.

MidcomNatBindMode.name: MidcomNatBindMode
MidcomNatBindMode.description: An indication whether the NAT bind is an address bind or an address-port bind.

MidcomNatBindId.name: MidcomNatBindId
MidcomNatBindId.description: A unique ID that is assigned to each NAT bind by a NAT enabled device.

MidcomNatSessionId.name: MidcomNatSessionId
MidcomNatSessionId.description: A unique ID that is assigned to each NAT session by a NAT enabled device.

midcomSrvResourceTable.name: midcomSrvResourceTable
midcomSrvResourceTable.description: This table lists all used middlebox resources per MIDCOM policy rule. The midcomSrvMBTable is indexed by session owner, group index, rule index.

midcomSrvResourceEntry.name: midcomSrvResourceEntry
midcomSrvResourceEntry.description: An entry describing a particular set of middlebox resources.

natSrcBindMode.name: natSrcBindMode
natSrcBindMode.description: An indication whether this policy rule uses an address NAT bind or an address-port NAT bind for the source address.

natSrcBindId.name: natSrcBindId
natSrcBindId.description: The allocated NAT bind for the source address used by this policy rule.

natDstBindMode.name: natDstBindMode
natDstBindMode.description: An indication whether this policy rule uses an address NAT bind or an address-port NAT bind for the destination address.

natDstBindId.name: natDstBindId
natDstBindId.description: The allocated NAT bind for the destination address used by this policy rule.

natSessionId1.name: natSessionId1
natSessionId1.description: A unique ID that is assigned to this specific NAT session at the NAT for this policy rule. A maximum of two NAT sessions can be assigned to one policy rule.

natSessionId2.name: natSessionId2
natSessionId2.description: A unique ID that is assigned to this specific NAT session at the NAT for this policy rule. A maximum of two NAT sessions can be assigned to one policy rule.

fwRuleId.name: fwRuleId
fwRuleId.description: A unique ID that is assigned to this specific firewall rule at the firewall for this policy rule.

midcomSrvFwTable.name: midcomSrvFwTable
midcomSrvFwTable.description: This table lists the firewal configuration per interface. The midcomSrvFwTable is indexed by midcomifIndex

midcomSrvFwEntry.name: midcomSrvFwEntry
midcomSrvFwEntry.description: An entry describing a particular set of firewall resources.

midcomifIndex.name: midcomifIndex
midcomifIndex.description: The corresponding interface of the middlebox.

fwGroup.name: fwGroup
fwGroup.description: The firewall rule group to which all firewall rules of the MIDCOM server are assigned.

fwPriority.name: fwPriority
fwPriority.description: The priority assigned to all firewall rules of the MIDCOM server.

midcomSrvSessionsRejected.name: midcomSrvSessionsRejected
midcomSrvSessionsRejected.description: The number of rejected MIDCOM sessions. The MIDCOM MIB module can rejected sessions that are not authorized or unknown.

midcomSrvSessionsCurrent.name: midcomSrvSessionsCurrent
midcomSrvSessionsCurrent.description: The number of currently established MIDCOM sessions. This object equals the number of rows in the midcomSessionTable and gives the number of MIDCOM agents (=SNMP managers) that are allowed to read, create, or modify entries in the MIDCOM MIB module.

midcomSrvSessionsTotal.name: midcomSrvSessionsTotal
midcomSrvSessionsTotal.description: The summarized number of all current and past established MIDCOM sessions.

midcomSrvRuleEntriesRejected.name: midcomSrvRuleEntriesRejected
midcomSrvRuleEntriesRejected.description: The number of policy rule entries rejected without any further detailed reason. Policy rules may be rejected due to several reasons. This object counts policy rules rejected without any other specific reason.

midcomSrvRulesIncomplete.name: midcomSrvRulesIncomplete
midcomSrvRulesIncomplete.description: The total number of policy rules that are incomplete. Policy rules are loaded via row entries in midcomRuleTable. This object counts policy rules that are loaded but not fully specified, i.e. the associated action (reserved or enable) is not set. Those rule are typically removed after sometime and counted.

midcomSrvResRulesRejected.name: midcomSrvResRulesRejected
midcomSrvResRulesRejected.description: The total number of reserved policy rules that are loaded, but are rejected.

midcomSrvResRulesFailed.name: midcomSrvResRulesFailed
midcomSrvResRulesFailed.description: The total number of failed reserved policy rules.

midcomSrvResRulesActive.name: midcomSrvResRulesActive
midcomSrvResRulesActive.description: The number of currently active reserved policy rules.

midcomSrvResRulesExpired.name: midcomSrvResRulesExpired
midcomSrvResRulesExpired.description: The number of currently expired reserved policy rules.

midcomSrvResRulesTerminated.name: midcomSrvResRulesTerminated
midcomSrvResRulesTerminated.description: The number of currently terminated reserved policy rules.

midcomSrvResRulesOnRequest.name: midcomSrvResRulesOnRequest
midcomSrvResRulesOnRequest.description: The number of currently on-request reserved policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesRejected.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesRejected
midcomSrvEnabledRulesRejected.description: The total number of rejected enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesFailed.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesFailed
midcomSrvEnabledRulesFailed.description: The total number of failed enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesActive.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesActive
midcomSrvEnabledRulesActive.description: The number of currently active enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesExpired.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesExpired
midcomSrvEnabledRulesExpired.description: The number of currently expired enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesTerminated.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesTerminated
midcomSrvEnabledRulesTerminated.description: The number of currently terminated enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvEnabledRulesOnRequest.name: midcomSrvEnabledRulesOnRequest
midcomSrvEnabledRulesOnRequest.description: The number of currently on-request enabled policy rules.

midcomSrvTransRejected.name: midcomSrvTransRejected
midcomSrvTransRejected.description: The total number of rejected transactions.

midcomSrvTransFailed.name: midcomSrvTransFailed
midcomSrvTransFailed.description: The total number of failed transactions.

midcomSrvTransCompleted.name: midcomSrvTransCompleted
midcomSrvTransCompleted.description: The total number of completed transactions.

midcomSrvCompliance.name: midcomSrvCompliance
midcomSrvCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities that implement the MIDCOM SERVER MIB.

midcomSrvResourceGroup.name: midcomSrvResourceGroup
midcomSrvResourceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the used NAT resources.

midcomSrvFwGroup.name: midcomSrvFwGroup
midcomSrvFwGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information about the used firewall resources.

midcomSrvStatisticsGroup.name: midcomSrvStatisticsGroup
midcomSrvStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistical information about the MIDCOM server.
